load the featurized data which includes all unified ATACseq peaks with 10 or more methylation reads. Values are average methylation levels in region.

methRegion=readRDS("Data/methFeatures.RDS")

load the annotations

methRegion.table=readRDS("Data/methFeatureTable.RDS")

load the phenotype information

phenoRegion=readRDS("Data/pheno.RDS")

load the ATAC data, we will use this to compare the signal only

atac=readRDS("Data/atac.RDS")

Compare ATAC and methylation signal

compute correlation

iim=match(rownames(methRegion), rownames(atac))
iinotna=which(!is.na(iim))
allCors=double(ncol(methRegion))
for(i in 1:ncol(methRegion)){
allCors[i]=cor(methRegion[iinotna,i], atac[iim[iinotna],i], use="p", method="s")
}
df=phenoRegion
df$cor=allCors
ggboxplot(df, x="tissue", y="cor", facet.by = "Sex")+theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1))

Normalize data and remove outliers

perform quantile normalization

methRegionQN=normalizeQuantiles(methRegion)

Visualize the PCA. We will precompute the SVD

set.seed(1); methRegionQN.svd=rsvd(tscale(methRegionQN), k=10)
plotPCAggplot(svdres = methRegionQN.svd, grp=phenoRegion$tissue, grp2=phenoRegion$Sex, do.contour = F)

get rid of tissue and sex to perform outlier tests

methRegionR=removeVars(methRegionQN,  model.matrix(~1+phenoRegion$tissue*phenoRegion$Sex))

New SVD on the residual data

set.seed(1);methRegionR.svd=rsvd(tscale(methRegionR),10)

Perform outlier tests and plot them onto the PCA This is a very conservative cutoff of Bonferroni corrected p-value of 0.01.

     poutRegion=outlierTest(svdin = methRegionR.svd)
      plotPCAggplotAll(svdres=methRegionR.svd, grp=as.factor(iioutliersRegion<-(poutRegion<0.01/400)), do.contour = F)

      iioutliersRegion=which(iioutliersRegion)

Remove outliers for all subsequent analysis

      methRegionQN=methRegionQN[, -iioutliersRegion]
      methRegion=methRegion[, -iioutliersRegion]
      methRegionR=methRegionR[, -iioutliersRegion]
      phenoRegion=phenoRegion[-iioutliersRegion,]

Filter un-informative regions based on SVD variance explained. This will be used later for the LV analysis and it may improve differential analysis.

k=5
      lvdatRegion=tscale(methRegionR) #this scales to 0 mean, variance one so error is exactly R2
   
      set.seed(1);lvdatRegion.svd=rsvd(lvdatRegion, k=k)
      
      err=rowMeans((lvdatRegion-SVDreconstruct(lvdatRegion.svd,k))^2) #this can be treated as R2
      
      
      
      n=ncol(lvdatRegion) #computing adjustment for adjusterd R2
      adj=n/(n-k)
      varE=1-err*adj
selected.featuresRegion=which(varE>0.1)
length(selected.featuresRegion)
## [1] 4578

Perform limma differential analysis using a wrapper function. This takes a long time on the entire matrix

limresRegion=fitLimma(vRegion, phenoRegion$group4, tcont)

limresRegionVar=fitLimma(vRegion[selected.featuresRegion,], phenoRegion$group4, tcont)
